
[1]lapidary

   LAP'IDARY, n. [L. lapidarius, lapis, a stone.]

   1. An artificer who cuts precious stones.

   2. A dealer in precious stones.

   3. A virtuoso skilled in the nature and kinds of gems or precious
   stones.

     LAP'IDARY, a. Pertaining to the art of cutting stones. The lapidary
         style denotes that which is proper for monumental and other
                                inscriptions.
